   realizations of a chiral crystal. We have studied by spin- and
   angle-resolved photoelectron spectroscopy its unconventional electronic
   structure and unique spin texture. We identify Kramers-Weyl, composite,
   and accordionlike Weyl fermions, so far only predicted by theory, and
   show that the spin polarization is parallel to the wave vector along the
