   special focus on the bands with a predominately d-orbital character.
   Using a light polarization analysis, the e(g) and t(2g) bands are
   identified across these materials. A clear correlation between the
   d(3z2-r2) band energy and the apical oxygen distance d(A) is
   demonstrated. Moreover, the compound dependence of the d(x2-y2) band
   bottom and the t(2g) band top is revealed. A direct comparison to
   density functional theory (DFT) calculations employing hybrid
   exchange-correlation functionals demonstrates excellent agreement. We
   thus conclude that the DFT methodology can be used to describe the
   global band structure of overdoped single-layer cuprates on both the
